一、圖書作者與內容簡介：<BR>
   Soman Chainani is an American author and filmmaker.<br />
<br />
    In a village, two girls were kidnapped to the School for Good and Evil, unlike what they expected, Agatha, the ugly one, went to the School for Good, and Sophie, the beautiful one, went to the School for Evil. In the end, their friendship brought them home.<br />
<br />

<BR>
二、內容摘錄：<BR>
    “Gently Agatha touched her face in the mirror, glowing from inside. A face no one recognized because it was so happy. There could be no turning back now. The bread crumbs on the dark trail were gone. Instead, she had the truth to guide her. A truth greater than any magic.I’ve been beautiful all along.” (p457)<br />
<br />
“Only once you destroy who you think you are can you embrace who you truly are.” (p134)<br />
<br />

<BR>
三、我的觀點：<BR>
    School for Good and Evil is a thrilling story of friendship, betrayal, magic, and romance. Join Sophie and Agatha, each other’s best friends and arch enemies, as they embark on their mission. Reading this book overturned my old ways of thinking.<br />
<br />
    Usually, we are often led to associate beauty with virtue and ugliness as villainy. However, this book overturned my prejudice. This is the reason I was so intrigued by this story. There is a saying, “Don’t judge a book by its cover.” this also applies to people. Though Agatha is ugly, she is fair at heart. On the other hand, Sophie is beautiful, but her soul is rotten and black, which tells us that fair complexion is not everything. From the day our generation was born, Disney stories have modified our thinking of good and evil, good is not just about beauty or show, and nor is evil just about ugliness and scratchy voices. I know now that I should not idolize those who are prettier than me. Instead, I should focus on the inner me. Like what Agatha said, pure good is what is on the inside, charity, kindness, love. I learned that having a kind and open heart is more important than outer appearance. Soman Chainani, the author of the School of Good and Evil, said that he wrote this book to tell us that we have been Disneyfied, and this story is meant to remind us Good means fitting in and Evil means difference. Thus we shouldn’t judge by appearance.<br />
<br />
    Albert Einstein once said, “Unthinking respect for authority is the greatest enemy of truth.”There are two opposing schools in this story. In the school for good, they teach the students how to be kind, how to be brave and chivalrous, and how to help others in need. However, in the school for evil, the students learn how to be evil, mean, jealous, and fill their hearts with hatred. If this school were real, students would influence each other. I think the reason the author chose to set the story at a school is we learn everything there. School is a place that teaches us knowledge, and the teachers pass on their ways of thinking and logic. Usually, we just soak it all up without thinking if it is right or wrong. It affects the ways we act and think. In my opinion, we should use our own logic to think about things, and not necessarily think by the way we are taught.<br />
<br />
    A friend in need is a friend indeed. Sophie and Agatha were best friends, and even though Sophie turned into a witch, their friendship overpowered it. During my time in elementary school, I transferred to a new school. I felt very frightened and lost, fortunately I met new friends who helped me fit in. They were kind and smart. They were the reason for my excitement to get to school. They helped me with school work I didn’t understand. That was when I realized how important friendship is. <br />
<br />
    To my astonishment, when I researched the author, Soman Chainani, I found out that Soman Chainani was actually a male! Before I found out, I had assumed a female had written it, because the main characters were two girls, and it was written in a feminine manner. From this, I  realized that I actually have prejudice too. Albeit unconsciously, it was still there. This book is all about bias, bias against what good and evil means, prejudice against prince and princesses. At the end of the story, instead of a prince saving a princess, a princess saved the witch. It told me that being a girl doesn’t mean having to wait for a prince to rescue me. Instead, being a girl, I can make my own decisions, be the heroin, and carve out a life of my own without help, which was why this book drove me to give a hand to those in need. This summer, I hosted a camp at a suburban elementary school and taught students English in a fun way. In the suburbs, there are not many learning resources, so I wanted to help them. Though it was challenging and exhausting, it was worth it. Their joyful smiles warmed my heart, and brought tears to my eyes. This, I knew, was what being good felt like giving charity with my full devotion.<br />
<br />

<BR>
四、討論議題：<BR>
    Bias is a part of the human condition — prejudice against good and evil, or bias against beauty and ugliness. We look at things with prejudice, we judge before we know, which makes us blind to the truth. So should we judge before knowing the truth?<br />
<br />

